	   <a name=102574699554570></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f102574699554570><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=102574699554570>RE: Best Tank pet</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=102574699554570#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=162723><span id=Scholar>Shaggur</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>44 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Jul 3rd 9:53 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.32]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>My mage is now 56 and the only time I use an earth pet for tanking is when I am solo'ing and root is a must. For just about every situation the air pet is best. I like to give my air pet a gnoll hide whip in his main and a dagger of dropping in his off. This gives him a double stun and the dagger weakens the mob which is a nice taunt. <br>Air pet is monk based so he has the highest AC of them all and even though hitpoints aren't as high as the earth pet he get hit much less often so he lives longer.<br>Basically if you let your pet die you are in BIG trouble while soloing. Mages get no root and no snare...crystaline webs hardly ever stick... so you had better start running.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
